section.section:
"Commercial use airport" means a publicly or privately owned airport at which:
Landing or tie down fees are charged;
Aviation fuel or oil is sold;
Space is rented;
Goods or services are sold; or
Other activities are carried out for remuneration.

A county or municipal corporation containing a commercial or public use airport may:
Establish a policy for preserving land for airports;
Establish airport districts;
Acquire an easement for development rights in an airport district;
Alter or abolish an easement in an airport district; and
Promote the preservation of airports in the county or municipal corporation by offering information and assistance to affected landowners with respect to the establishment of an airport district and the purchase of an easement.

In designating land as an airport district or acquiring an easement in an airport district, a county or municipal corporation shall:
Solicit from the county or municipal corporation planning and zoning body a study of the impact of an easement before acquiring an easement in an airport district;
Consider current local regulations;
Consider local patterns of land development; and
Consider local priorities for the preservation of airport land.
